The <b>Rufous-bellied Chachalaca</b> (<i><b>Ortalis wagleri</b></i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cracidae" title="Cracidae">Cracidae</a> family. It is found only in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>. Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical dry <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a> and subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests.
